From: diaaney <av6cts@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 10:27:07 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] rapier - 1.8 combat: restore full horizontal KB to blockers

user reports blockhit target only gets vertical KB, not horizontal.
server math applies both components via knockback(0.4F, d, d1) but
some interaction damps the horizontal visually. add a second impulse
directly to deltaMovement when target is a blocker with partial block,
and hurtMarked=true again to force a second velocity sync packet.
authentic 1.8 blockers took full normal KB magnitude.

diff --git a/net/minecraft/world/entity/LivingEntity.java b/net/minecraft/world/entity/LivingEntity.java
index 78f7a0788c22c66da37ee14e03c7947b6b140595..790cd3ea667b3242301b2a24ea7b28e66ab7020c 100644
--- a/net/minecraft/world/entity/LivingEntity.java
+++ b/net/minecraft/world/entity/LivingEntity.java
@@ -1541,6 +1541,15 @@ public abstract class LivingEntity extends Entity implements Attackable, Waypoin
                     // Paper end - Check distance in entity interactions
 
                     this.knockback(0.4F, d, d1, damageSource.getDirectEntity(), damageSource.getDirectEntity() == null ? io.papermc.paper.event.entity.EntityKnockbackEvent.Cause.DAMAGE : io.papermc.paper.event.entity.EntityKnockbackEvent.Cause.ENTITY_ATTACK); // CraftBukkit // Paper - knockback events
+                    // rapier - 1.8 combat: blockers sometimes render with only vertical KB visible because the client damps horizontal velocity for a using-item player. re-apply the horizontal component directly to deltaMovement and re-mark so a second motion packet lands on top. authentic 1.8 blockers took identical KB magnitude to non-blockers.
+                    if (flag && f1 < originAmount && this.isBlocking()) {
+                        double rapierBlockKbMag = Math.sqrt(d * d + d1 * d1);
+                        if (rapierBlockKbMag > 1.0E-5) {
+                            net.minecraft.world.phys.Vec3 rapierBlockDelta = this.getDeltaMovement();
+                            this.setDeltaMovement(rapierBlockDelta.x - (d / rapierBlockKbMag) * 0.4, rapierBlockDelta.y, rapierBlockDelta.z - (d1 / rapierBlockKbMag) * 0.4);
+                            this.hurtMarked = true;
+                        }
+                    }
                     if (!flag) {
                         this.indicateDamage(d, d1);
                     }
